@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api

### 1) Register (creates user + returns tokens)
# @name register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "Password123",
  "firstName": "Alex",
  "lastName": "River"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.accessToken);
    client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.refreshToken);
%}

### 2) Login (returns tokens)
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "Password123"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.accessToken);
    client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.refreshToken);
%}

### 3) Me (reads user info from access token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 4) Refresh (exchange refresh token for new tokens)
# @name refresh
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/refresh
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "refreshToken": "{{refreshToken}}"
}

> {%
    client.global.set("accessToken", response.body.accessToken);
    client.global.set("refreshToken", response.body.refreshToken);
%}

### 5) Me using refreshed access token
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### 6) Logout (invalidates refresh tokens for this user)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/logout
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
